Hello Niels,

As far as I can see, these are the ways a crawl can pause itself
spontaneously

- with the RuntimeLimitEnforcer processor
- LowDiskPauseProcessor or DiskSpaceMonitor
- in case of a serious error like OutOfMemoryError

If you don&#39;t have any of those modules configured (none of them are by
default), then it must be the serious error case. There should be a stack
trace in your heritrix_out.

If it&#39;s OOME then you can bump up your heap size or reduce the number of
toe threads in your job.

Noah


